summary:
I kicked off my career in journalism and then moved to the translation and localisation industry. I have always been a lover of languages and I’m skilled in intercultural communication, linguistics, translation and localisation. But then my love for organising stuff kicked in and I decided to make a shift. 

I've been working with content at Booking.com for five years now. As a Senior Coordinator, I oversee the content production for an ever-growing number of projects and products throughout Booking.com. I work with numerous stakeholders, connecting them with our content solutions – from product descriptions, to destination content and SEO – created by in-house and external writers, as well as machine-generated content.
